headline: Has the Market Rerated Trimble Too Far After Its Geospatial and Construction Tech Push?
summary: Wondering if Trimble at around $80 a share is still a smart buy or if the easy money has already been made? Let us break down what the market is really pricing in so you can judge the value for yourself. Trimble has slipped about 1.2% over the last week, but is still up 3.8% over the past month and an impressive 15.5% year to date, with a 63.8% gain over three years suggesting the long term story has been working.
